		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.24]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Debalic&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Pet toys are anything you give to a pet to increase their usefulness. Basically a Mage can summon gear, like sets of Phantom armor and various weapons. Most pets, including charmed, will put these items to use.<br /><br />Lower-level pets have some interesting tricks. The pet will use its innate base damage, unless it has a weapon whose damage is greater. They ignore delay. So, if a 1st level Necromancer pet hits for 6 dmg, and I give him a Rusty Scythe (dmg 8) he'll use that dmg. (that was my favorite; mowing down Orcs in Greater Fay with a scythe-wielding skelly pet!) I also have been giving my BST's pet Crude Bone Halberds. <br /><br />Later on, pets will start to dual-wield, albeit at a low skill) around 24-29. Some pets can be forced to dual-wield by giving them two weapons; at this point the dmg would be irrelevant and rusty daggers would work. <br /><br />Eventually, pets dual wield on their own and have decent damage output. What you can do is give them weapons that proc - some higher-level Mage summons do; also Velium weapons are popular for this. <br /><br />Then there's the special bits mentioned above, the collars and mask with +HP and haste. <br /><br />You can sometimes find Mages in PoK or the Bazaar, willing to sell summoned gear. </p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Dear President Bush,<br /><br />Please don't get us all killed.<br /><br />Yours (for another four years),<br />The American People</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from New York (no, not the city)</td></tr></table>
